HEADWORD: Glossopharyngeal
<hw>Glos`so*phar`yn*ge"al</hw>
<pr>(gl⟦ocr⟧s"d⟦osl⟧*f⟦acr⟧r`⟦icr⟧n*j⟦emac⟧"⟦ait⟧l <it>or</it>
gl⟦ocr⟧s"d⟦osl⟧*f⟦adot⟧*r⟦icr⟧n"j⟦esl⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>glw^ssa</grk> the tongue + E.
<ets>pharyngeal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to both
the tongue and the pharynx; -- applied especially to the ninth pair of
cranial nerves, which are distributed to the pharynx and tongue.</def>
-- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the glossopharyngeal
nerves.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

